\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\i\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i\b0 Geographic market}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [8]\tab The geographical market is considered to be national for all the relevant products markets which are manufactured, distributed and supplied nationally. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\b\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\b {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b COMPETITION EVALUATION}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [9]\tab In the market for pre-painted or textured steel sheeting/ colour coated sheeting or tiles where there is a  limited horizontal overlap, Macsteel Roofing has 22% market share pre-merger and HRP has less than 1% market share.  Post merger, they will have
 a combined market share of around 23% in this market. There are no horizontal concerns given the insignificant market share accretion in this market.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [10]\tab However, the Tribunal raised concerns that Harvey\'91s tiles have 55% of the steel tile market. At the hearing, Miss Finesse from Harvey submitted that there are other domestic players such as Rollco which has 25% market share, Pro Roof 10%, Global Roofi
ng Solution 5% and other domestic suppliers including international suppliers, which are highly competitive despite not having very high market shares. In addition the merging parties submitted that the steel tile market is not a capital intensive industry
, and that the barriers to entry in this industry are low.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [11]\tab The Tribunal further raised concerns about any possibility of margin squeeze that might arise due to Macsteel\'92s relationship with Mittal. However the Commission submitted that other merchants also have access to Mittal\'92s coil, and that there are no ma
jor concerns given Mittal\'92s current best buy policy of smaller volumes which has had the impact of bringing in more merchants that are able to supply downstream tile manufacturers. There is also no evidence that Mittal is favouring Macsteel in the domestic
 market.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [12]\tab  At the hearing Mr Pimstein, Chief Executive of Macsteel  also submitted that Mittal\'92s policy of smaller volumes has invited in smaller customers to deal directly with Mittal, and that this has resulted in smaller customers buying at higher volume lev
els, which means that even if this policy changed, it will not have any negative impact on  them since they are already buying  higher volumes at the most competitive levels in the Mittal matrix, which is easily accessible to all.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\ql\rtlch\af6\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs22\lang1033\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [13]\tab In the vertical analysis, we concur with the Commission that there are no customer foreclosure concerns as Harvey does not purchase galvanized steel sheets from any other supplier other than from MSC. The merging parties submitted that there are no in
put foreclosure concerns as Harvey only purchases 13% of MSC\'92s total supply of galvanized steel sheets and will be unable to absorb all of MSC\'92s supply of galvanized steel sheets. The merging parties further submitted that there are other parties that coul
d supply Pristine Tiles, MSC\'92s only customer in this market, with its required product in this market.  The Commission also interviewed several merchants in the market, such as Pro Roof, Trident Steel, Steelrode, and Gibb Steel who averred that they have c
apacity to supply the same service to independent tile manufacturers.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sa200\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\b\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\b {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033\i0\b CONCLUSION}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af6\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f6\fs20\lang1033\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f6\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 [14]\tab In light of the above, we find that this merger will not result in a substantial lessening or prevention of competition in any of the relevant markets.  Accordingly, we approve the merger without conditions.  }
